sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Returns events on the specified calendar.

Inputs:

  • Calendar ID - Calendar identifier ID. If you want to access the primary calendar of the currently logged in user, use the "primary" keyword.
  • Start Time - Upper bound (exclusive) for an event's start time to filter by.
  • End Time - Lower bound (exclusive) for an event's end time to filter by.
  • Search Term - Free text search terms to find events that match these terms in any field, except for extended properties.

Outputs:

  • Events - Data Object with array of events as items.
    • Summary - Title of the event.
    • ID - Event identifier ID.

To use this action, the corresponding Google Calendar connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Calendar Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Look Up Hangouts Meetings
